Police in Thika town on Tuesday fired tear gas to to disperse two matatu factions that were fighting over a terminus. The 2TS and 254 Finest saccos that ply the Thika-Makongeni route have for more than eight months been embroiled in a row over a terminus. Their standoff went a notch higher when crews from both saccos engaged in a fistfight, disrupting operations in the town. Touts, drivers and officials exchanged blows and kicks, but officers from Thika police station arrived on time to stop the brawl. The 2TS officials accused the 254 Finest Sacco of planning to ‘hijack’ their customers.  